def: A toper; a guzzler. See Boozer.
Deviation from the true order of time; anachronism. [R.]Selden.

Uttered with voice; pronounced with vibrations of the vocalcords; sonant; -- said of a sound uttered with the glottis narrowed.Voiced stop, Voice stop (Phon.), a stopped consonant made with tonefrom the larynx while the mouth organs are closed at some point; asonant mute, as b, d, g hard.
Any plant of the genus Veronica, mostly low herbs with paleblue corollas, which quickly fall off.
In a sore manner; grievously; painfully; as, to be sorelyafflicted.
An instrument for measuring the depth of the color of anything,especially of a liquid, by comparison with a standard liquid.

To cut roughly or hack; to cut into small pieces; to notch orcut in an unskillful manner; to make rough or mangle by cutting; as,a boy haggles a stick of wood.Suffolk first died, and York, all haggled o'er, Comes to him, wherein gore he lay insteeped. Shak.
An emerald-green variety of spodumene found in North Carolina;lithia emerald, -- used as a gem.
Woe; torment; pain. [Obs.] "Pyne of hell." Chaucer.
Having three knots or nodes; having three points from which aleaf may shoot; as, a trinodal stem.
